Reasoning: The paper discusses the neural basis of visual search and decision-making, which involves topics such as neural networks, computer vision, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses images and firing rate vectors, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The decision-theoretic formulation and hypothesis testing also suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
